brooklyn.event.basic
[Java] Class MapConfigKey

java.lang.Object
  brooklyn.event.basic.BasicConfigKey
      brooklyn.event.basic.AbstractStructuredConfigKey
          brooklyn.event.basic.MapConfigKey

public class MapConfigKey
extends AbstractStructuredConfigKey

A config key which represents a map, where contents can be accessed directly via subkeys. Items added directly to the map must be of type map, and can be updated by:

  • Putting individual subkeys (SubElementConfigKey)
  • Passing an an appropriate MapModification from MapModifications to clear, clear-and-set, or update
  • Setting a value against a dot-extension of the key (e.g. setting a.map.subkey=1 will cause getConfig(a.map[type=MapConfigKey]) to return {subkey=1}; but note the above are preferred where possible)
  • Setting a map directly against the MapConfigKey (but note that the above are preferred where possible)
